CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 5, 1955, pg. 21B, reads: "Reflections on Life - Looking down on the city and the spot where he used to live, Ray Saunders reflects that his early life in Gazzam Hill, 'a spot of country in city' had a great influence in shaping him into an artist. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Raymond "Ray" Saunders seated on railing, and woman, posed on balcony looking toward Downtown from Hill District
